The paper discusses a method for compressing deep learning models, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The use of simulation and iterative pruning suggests a focus on optimization and efficiency, which is often discussed in the context of large-scale computing and distributed systems (cs.DC). However, the focus on deep learning and the evaluation of the proposed method using experiments suggests a stronger connection to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
